msgid "To group dimension values and create an :guilabel:`Others` category:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:314
msgid ""
"Hold `Ctrl` then select the cells of the row or column dimension values that "
"should be grouped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:315
msgid ""
"Right-click one of the selected cells, then click :icon:`fa-plus-square-"
"o` :guilabel:`Group pivot dimensions`. A new dimension is added to "
"the :guilabel:`Columns` or :guilabel:`Rows` section, as relevant. Change the "
"sorting to :guilabel:`Ascending` or :guilabel:`Descending`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:318
msgid "On the card of the new dimension:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:320
msgid ""
"Change the :guilabel:`Order by` field from :guilabel:`Unsorted` "
"to :guilabel:`Ascending` or :guilabel:`Descending`, as desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:322
msgid ""
"Click :icon:`fa-angle-right` :guilabel:`Groups` to expand the sub-section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:323
msgid ""
"Optionally, rename :guilabel:`Group` by clicking it and entering a new name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:324
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`+ \"Others\"` group to have the unselected dimension values "
"added to a single group that is then placed after the selected values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:327
msgid ""
"To collapse or expand a dimension group in the pivot table, click "
"the :icon:`fa-plus-square-o` :guilabel:`(expand)` or :icon:`fa-minus-square-"
"o` :guilabel:`(collapse)` icon as relevant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/productivity/spreadsheet/work_with_data/pivot_tables.rst:331
msgid ""
"In the example, data per salesperson for the secondary markets of Spain, "
